Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(stalks and all).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest then juice @lime{1/2}(zested and juiced) (double for 4p).

Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop into 2cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary!

Meanwhile, pour @cold salted water{300%ml}(double for 4p) into a medium #pot{}
with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, place a separate pot over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @cashews{20%g} and dry-fry until lightly toasted, stirring
regularly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once toasted, transfer to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Return the pot to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily!

Add the mushrooms to the pot, season with salt and pepper and fry until
golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @korma curry paste{1%sachet} and cook until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Add @coconut milk{1%pack}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @peanut butter{1%sachet}
and @water{150%ml} (double for 4p). Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower heat to medium-low and simmer until sauce has reduced by
half, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir the roasted aubergine into the curry. Remove the pot from the heat.

Stir in the lime juice and half the coriander then season to taste with salt
and pepper.

Fluff up the rice with the #fork{}, stir through the lime zest and divide
between #bowls{}.

Top with the creamy mushroom curry.

Finish with a sprinkling of cashews and the remaining coriander.